dc_title_s: Africa, central part of Somali country, Province Ogadayn, from a survey by F. L. James, Esqre
dc_description_s: Includes inset panel: Continuation southward on the same scale, from native information. Shows approximate course of Shebelle River between Ha-Wadly and Madisha [Mogadishu], and portion of Indian Ocean coastline. Roads and travel routes, including days travel between destinations, are shown. Includes information on groundwater and vegetation. Route of expedition shown in red. From: Proceedings of the Royal Geographical Society and monthly record of geography. Vol. 7 (1885), no. 10, pp. 625-46; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J6873
